# Module Conventions

## ESM

This project uses ECMAScript Modules (`"type": "module"`). `verbatimModuleSyntax` is enabled.

- All relative imports MUST use `.js` extensions.
- Type-only imports MUST use `import type`.

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { TopicKey } from "../../types.js";
import type { SystemConfig } from "./index.js";

// ❌ Missing extension
import { TopicKey } from "../../types";

// ❌ Non-type import used only as a type
import { SystemConfig } from "./index.js";
```

## Seed Data Files

- `src/_seed/system-config.ts` — Static system definition (what governs behavior). Imports from `../index.js`.
- `src/_seed/system-state.ts` — Initial runtime snapshot (what exists at first boot). Imports from `../index.js`.
- Both use runtime enum values (`TopicKey.Calendar`, not `"calendar"`).
- These are seed files — they populate the database on `--seed` and never change at runtime. See `seed-data.mdc` for full constraints.

## Enums Over String Literals

All classified values use their enum. Never use raw strings where an enum exists.
